title: St. Paul's tube station entrance
description: St. Paul's tube station is a London Underground stop on the Central Line in Zone 1. title: The Monument
description:
The Monument to the Great Fire of London, more commonly known as The Monument is a 61-metre (202-foot) tall stone Roman doric column in the City of London, near to the northern end of London Bridge. It is located at the junction of Monument Street and Fish Street Hill, 61 metres from where the Great Fire of London started in 1666.

http://www.ianvisits.co.uk/gallery/v/monument/

urlhtml: Lock, Stock and Two Smoking Barrels - Filming Location
title: Lock, Stock and Two Smoking Barrels - Filming Location
description:
Lock, Stock and Two Smoking Barrels is a 1998 British crime film directed and written by Guy Ritchie. The story is a heist film involving a self-confident young card sharp who loses £500,000 to a powerful crime lord in a rigged game of three card brag. In order to pay off his debts, he and his friends decide to rob a small-time gang who happen to be operating out of the flat next door. The film garnered Guy Ritchie international acclaim, and introduced actors Vinnie Jones, a former Welsh international football player, and Jason Statham, to worldwide audiences.

This house was used for the hideout.

title: Paul's Cross
description: A grandiose Victorian re-creation of the medieval preaching cross which stood near this spot until the Reformation.   Paul's Cross was the scene of important and controversial open-air sermons in the 16th century and may have been an ancient meeting place of London people, possibly dating back to Saxon times.
